@node Introduction "AquaPWFail v1.0 Documentation"

Introduction
~~~~~~~~~~~~
AquaPWFail is a password failure door. You know, one that will be started
when a user has failed 3 times in a row to enter his password correctly.
It has lots of nice and useful @{"features" Link Features}...
@endnode

@node Features "AquaPWFail v1.0 Documentation"

Features
~~~~~~~~
* Auto-messages to sysop(s). It can automatically post a message to any
  number of users, informing about the password failure - who, when,
  where and the connect string. Why show the connect string then? Well you
  might be able to conclude from that if it was someone who tried to hack
  the account. For example, if it was an HST connect and you know that the
  user owning the account has a pure V.32bis modem, then you should be
  very suspicious...

* Auto-message to user (optional of course). If it wasn't the user owning
  the account who made the password failure, it could be interesting for
  him to be informed about it. You can configure what the 'from' field in
  the message header should read. If you let it be your handle, the user
  can reply and explain to you about his password failure or tell you that
  it wasn't him...

* Last-password-failures bulletin. The door can create a nice-looking
  bulletin showing the last password failures (configurable number of
  entries). Besides it being a funny thing to view, it is good for
  users to check there now and then. If they are listed in the bulletin
  but haven't received any message from AquaPWFail (presuming that you
  have 'Auto-message to user' on) the hacker probably succeeded to hack
  his account and deleted the message.

* Special password failure log. If you want, the door can write to a log
  (anywhere you like) about the password failure.

* Page or leave comment. When the user has failed 3 times to enter his
  password and then enters the door, he is given these options:

        (1) Page Sysop
        (2) Comment to Sysop
        (Q) Hangup

  This menu is shown repeatedly until Q is chosen.

* Working comment function! Unlike in many other pwfail doors, the
  'Comment to Sysop' function really works 100%. If you want several
  users (for example yourself and some co-sysop) to receive the same
  comments, that's no problem.

* Special built-in pager! When the user selects 'Page Sysop' assuming
  you're "available" or you have configured that pwfail-users can override
  the chatflag, the paging starts: A font-sensitive operator window opens
  on the default public screen (which usually is Workbench). It has a
  graphical progress bar which goes from 0% to 100% during the paging.
  There is a progress bar on the user side as well. The window has three
  buttons: 'Go into Chat', 'Be Quiet' and 'Deny Chat'. Pressing <Escape>
  or clicking in the close gadget has the same function as pressing 'Be
  Quiet'. Pressing <Enter> means 'Go into Chat'. There are also ordinary
  hotkeys for every button.
@endnode

@node Requirements "AquaPWFail v1.0 Documentation"

Requirements
~~~~~~~~~~~~
- An Amiga with OS 2.04 or higher.

- AmiExpress, SigmaExpress or any compatible program.
@endnode

@node Installation "AquaPWFail v1.0 Documentation"

Installation
~~~~~~~~~~~~
Just copy the 'AquaPWFail' directory (the inner one) to 'Doors:', and
(for /X 3.0+) put the provided command icon 'PWFAIL.info' in your 'SYSCmd'
drawer.

The door is "pure" and is therefore safe to make resident.

The text 'Doors:AquaPWFail/Comment.txt' will be displayed when the user
choses to leave a comment to the sysop. Edit it if you like.

If 'Doors:AquaPWFail/BullText.txt' exists, it will be inserted in the
last-password-failures bulletin.

Now you must @{"configure" Link Configuration} the door...
@endnode

@node Configuration "AquaPWFail v1.0 Documentation"

Tooltypes in 'Doors:AquaPWFail/AquaPWFail.info':
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
       @{" SYSOP_MSGBASE   " Link SYSOP_MSGBASE}
       @{" AUTOMAIL.x      " Link AUTOMAIL.x}
       @{" COMMENT.x       " Link COMMENT.x}
       @{" USER_MSGBASE    " Link USER_MSGBASE}
       @{" TO_USER_FROM    " Link TO_USER_FROM}
       @{" LOG_PATH        " Link LOG_PATH}
       @{" BULL_PATH       " Link BULL_PATH}
       @{" BULL_USERS      " Link BULL_USERS}
       @{" CHATFLAG_IGNORE " Link CHATFLAG_IGNORE}
       @{" PAGE_BEEP       " Link PAGE_BEEP}
       @{" QUIETPOP        " Link QUIETPOP}
       @{" PAGESTART_RUN   " Link PAGESTART_RUN}
       @{" PAGESTOP_RUN    " Link PAGESTOP_RUN}

@endnode

@node SYSOP_MSGBASE "AquaPWFail v1.0 Documentation"

Template: SYSOP_MSGBASE=<path>                                  [Required]
Example : SYSOP_MSGBASE=BBS:CONF_Staff/MsgBase/

This tooltype specifies the message base directory where messages to
sysops will be written (see @{"AUTOMAIL.<num>" Link AUTOMAIL.x} and @{"COMMENT.<num>" Link COMMENT.x}). It MUST end
with '/' or ':'.
@endnode

@node AUTOMAIL.x "AquaPWFail v1.0 Documentation"

Template: AUTOMAIL.<num>=<name>                                 [Optional]
Example : AUTOMAIL.1=Aquarius

These tooltypes specify the users who will be notified of every password
failure: a message will automatically be posted to them. No AUTOMAIL.<num>
tooltypes means that no auto-messages will be posted.
@endnode

@node COMMENT.x "AquaPWFail v1.0 Documentation"

Template: COMMENT.<num>=<name>                  [At least ONE is required]
Example : COMMENT.1=Aquarius

These tooltypes specify the users who will receive the comments written by
users in the door (when they have chosen "Comment to Sysop").
@endnode

@node USER_MSGBASE "AquaPWFail v1.0 Documentation"

Template: USER_MSGBASE=<path>                                   [Optional]
Example : USER_MSGBASE=BBS:CONF_NewUsers/MsgBase/

If this tooltype is present, the door will write a message to the user
himself. The tooltype specifies the path to the message base where the
message will be written. If it was someone who tried to hack his account
it could be helpful for him to know that. The path MUST end with '/' or
':'.
@endnode

@node TO_USER_FROM "AquaPWFail v1.0 Documentation"

Template: TO_USER_FROM=<string>       [Optional, default: AquaPWFail vX.X]
Example : TO_USER_FROM=Aquarius

This tooltype specifies the user (or any other string) that will stand as
sender in the auto-message to the user himself. If no @{"USER_MSGBASE" Link USER_MSGBASE}
tooltype is present, that message won't be posted, and this tooltype will
be ignored.
@endnode

@node LOG_PATH "AquaPWFail v1.0 Documentation"

Template: LOG_PATH=<path>                                       [Optional]
Example : LOG_PATH=Doors:AquaPWFail/AquaPWFail.Log

This tooltype specifies the path (including filename) where password
failures will be logged. If you leave this out, no log file will be
maintained.
@endnode

@node BULL_PATH "AquaPWFail v1.0 Documentation"

Template: BULL_PATH=<path>                                      [Optional]
Example : BULL_PATH=Doors:AquaPWFail/AquaPWFail.Bull

This tooltype specifies the path (including filename) where you want the
last-password-failures bulletin to be created. If you leave this out, no
bulletin will be made.
@endnode

@node BULL_USERS "AquaPWFail v1.0 Documentation"

Template: BULL_USERS=<number>                      [Optional, default: 10]
Example : BULL_USERS=12

This tooltype specifies the number of users that will be displayed in the
last-password-failures bulletin.
@endnode

@node CHATFLAG_IGNORE "AquaPWFail v1.0 Documentation"

Template: CHATFLAG_IGNORE=<YES|NO>                 [Optional, default: NO]
Example : CHATFLAG_IGNORE=YES

If you set this to YES, the "available-for-chat flag" will be ignored and
the user in the door will always be able to page you.
@endnode

@node PAGE_BEEP "AquaPWFail v1.0 Documentation"

Template: PAGE_BEEP=<YES|NO>                       [Optional, default: NO]
Example : PAGE_BEEP=YES

This tooltype lets you decide if you want the door to make system beeps
during paging.
@endnode

@node QUIETPOP "AquaPWFail v1.0 Documentation"

Template: QUIETPOP=<YES|NO>                        [Optional, default: NO]
Example : QUIETPOP=NO

This tooltype determines what should happen when you press the 'Be Quiet'
button in the operator window. If the AmiExpress screen should be popped
to front, set the tooltype to YES. If it is NO then the previously
frontmost screen will be brought to front and the previously active window
will be activated.
@endnode

@node PAGESTART_RUN "AquaPWFail v1.0 Documentation"

Template: PAGESTART_RUN=<CLI command>                           [Optional]
Example : PAGESTART_RUN=C:Player mod.nice

The command you write here will be executed when the paging starts. (It is
run asyncronously so the door doesn't wait for it to return.)
@endnode

@node PAGESTOP_RUN "AquaPWFail v1.0 Documentation"

Template: PAGESTOP_RUN=<CLI command>                            [Optional]
Example : PAGESTOP_RUN=C:KillPlayer

This command is executed when the operator window is closed (for any
reason).
@endnode

@node History "AquaPWFail v1.0 Documentation"

History
~~~~~~~

0.1 (12-26-94) First beta ready.


0.2 (12-30-94) Built-in pager finished! Thanks to Sandman for inspiration.


0.3 (12-30-94) It now works (can read connect string etc) if the
               callerslog contains the attempted password instead of
               "xxxx".

               Added tooltypes PAGESTART_RUN and PAGESTOP_RUN.


0.4 (01-09-95) If chat has been denied once, the user can't page again.
               Thanks to Ace Caze for the suggestion!

               Restructured the tooltypes somewhat:
                 Removed:
                   SYSOP.<num>=<...>
                 Added:
                   AUTOMAIL.<num>=<receiver of automsg>
                   COMMENT.<num>=<receiver of user comment>
                   TO_USER_FROM=<sender of msg to user>

               Time and date are now written in the body of the automsg
               to sysop(s) and msg to user.
               (I find it easier than having to look in the msg header.
               And if the user replies to the msg, the time & date will
               still be there, if he quotes.)

               Made a better-looking door title..

               Last pw failures bulletin!! Thanks to Dansken for bugging
               me about it. :)

               New tooltypes:
                 BULL_PATH=<bulletin filename>
                 BULL_USERS=<max # users in bulletin>

               "Doors:AquaPWFail/BullText.txt" is inserted in the
               bulletin...

               If there was error reading callerslog, time and date will
               be set to current, so no more "??:??:?? ??-??-??".

               It now writes "Please hold a second..." at the start while
               posting all messages, writing to the log and creating the
               bulletin.

               If BULL_USERS=1 then the bulletin title will be
               "LAST PASSWORD FAILURE" instead of "LAST 1 PASSWORD
               FAILURES".


1.0 (01-11-95) Removed unused code and fixed a few strings.

    (01-25-95) Fixed a gfx bug: The progress bar would grow a few pixels
               too wide.

    (01-28-95) First release!
@endnode

